The trial of Sandile Mantsoe, who allegedly killed his girlfriend Karabo Mokoena, was postponed on Friday to allow the court to hear testimony from people who retrieved CCTV footage from Sandton Sky apartments Judge AJ Johnson told the Prosecutor during proceedings at the South Gauteng High Court that he needed the people who handled the footage to be present in court and testify. Prior to that, the state had intended to show the court video footage of the events that occurred before Mokoena was allegedly killed. READ MORE: ‘Abusive’ Mantsoe back in court for alleged murder of girlfriend Karabo Mokoena In a statement on Thursday, Mantsoe claimed Mokoena committed suicide and had multiple sexual partners which lead to their break-up. Court was adjourned until Tuesday, 24 April. – African News Agency